children.subject: You can consider 133 as almost a 1-2 unit class (in terms of workload) if you've taken 61A/B (or even just 61A, but I guess exposure to data structures will be helpful with R data frames?). The only "time consuming" part of 133 will be getting used to R syntax/learning to use RStudio (which honestly can be done in less than a week), and if Gaston Sanchez is teaching it, the posts (pretty much mini research blogs written in md syntax) might take some time due to the nature of them being writing-heavy.
